{
  "texts": [
    "Image quality is critical for vision-based detectors, as low-quality images usually lead to poor detection results, especially in adverse weather conditions such as rain, snow, fog, or strong sunlight, all of which can negatively impact detection accuracy.Additionally, there are challenges related to detecting small objects, such as traffic lights and traffic signs, where the features may not be as distinct, leading to subpar detection performance.",
    "Consequently, conventional object detection algorithms may not meet the requirements of object detection and recognition in traffic scenarios, necessitating optimization and improvements in these algorithms.",
    "Currently, the optimization of object detection algorithms primarily focuses on four aspects: feature enhancement, leveraging contextual information, super-resolution techniques, and loss functions.",
    "The following sections will discuss research in optimizing object detection algorithms within each of these four areas.",
    "These methods for optimizing the loss function help to improve the performance of object detection algorithms in traffic scenes, especially when dealing with challenges such as small targets, dense target alignments, or occlusions."
  ]
}